<title>UK: Chloride finance director Vass to retire.</title>
<headline>Chloride finance director Vass to retire.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>British industrial group Chloride Group Plc said on Tuesday that group finance director Michael Vass has decided to retire at the end of August to &quot;devote more time to his family and personal interests&quot;.</p>
<p>Vass retires by rotation as a director following the annual general meeting on July 23 and will not seek re-election.</p>
<p>Vass will be succeeded by Neil Warner who joins the company on May 1 and takes up the post of group finance director on July 23. Warner recently spent six years at Ocean Group Plc, latterly as director of financial planning.</p>
